title: Junior React Developer - Web App Wizard (TRAP)
description:

This position requires a bachelor's degree in Computer Science or a related field, coupled with 5+ years of professional experience using React, Redux, and related technologies. You will also be responsible for mentoring junior developers and leading small projects.

## Responsibilities

- Architect and implement complex UI features using React, Redux, and TypeScript.
- Optimize application performance for speed and scalability.
- Collaborate with back-end engineers to integrate APIs.
- Lead code reviews and ensure code quality standards are met.
- Mentor junior developers and provide technical guidance.

**Tech Stack:** React, Redux, TypeScript, Node.js, GraphQL, AWS

**Benefits:**
- Generous salary and stock options.
- Comprehensive health insurance.
- Unlimited vacation policy.

title: Intern/Junior React Front-end Engineer - Unleash Your React Prowess

Looking for a React guru ready to take the front-end world by storm! We're seeking a driven and experienced React front-end engineer with minimum 5 years experience to architect and build scalable user interfaces. Your responsibilities include leading a team of junior developers, making key technical decisions, optimizing performance, and ensuring the highest levels of code quality. Expertise in TypeScript, Redux, and Next.js is mandatory. The successful candidate will also possess lead experience and strong communication skills. Join us and take your career to the next level!.

## Responsibilities

- Architect and implement complex UI features using React.
- Lead a team of junior developers.
- Make key technical decisions.
- Optimize performance.
- Ensure the highest levels of code quality.

**Tech Stack:** React, TypeScript, Redux, Next.js, Node.js, GraphQL

**Benefits:**
- Competitive salary (commensurate with experience).
- Comprehensive benefits package.
- Stock options in a rapidly growing company.

title: Lead Data Engineer - Cloud Solutions

DataWise Analytics is hiring a Lead Data Engineer to build and maintain our cloud-based data infrastructure. This is a fantastic opportunity to lead a team and work with cutting-edge technologies in a fast-paced environment. Join us in Prague or work remotely from anywhere in the world!

## Responsibilities:

- Design and implement data pipelines using cloud-native technologies (AWS, Azure, or GCP).
- Lead a team of data engineers and provide technical guidance.
- Implement data governance policies and ensure data quality.
- Work with large datasets and optimize query performance.
- Implement and maintain data warehousing solutions.
- Collaborate with data scientists to enable data-driven decision making.
- Automate data ingestion and processing workflows.

**Tech Stack:** Python, Spark, Hadoop, AWS, Azure, GCP, SQL, NoSQL databases, Airflow, dbt

**Benefits:** Competitive salary and bonus structure, generous vacation policy, remote work options, professional development opportunities, stock options, company-sponsored social events.

**Benefits:** Generous salary, performance-based bonuses, health insurance, professional development opportunities, and a collaborative work environment.

**Tech Stack:** Python, FastAPI, Docker, Kubernetes, Apache Kafka, Apache Spark, Postgres, AWS

**Benefits:** Competitive salary, stock options, flexible working hours, unlimited vacation, free snacks and drinks, and the opportunity to learn from the best in the field!

title: Lead QA Engineer - Championing Quality Across the Board
description:
Quality First is looking for a Lead QA Engineer to champion quality across our organization. You'll be responsible for leading the QA team, defining testing strategies, and ensuring the delivery of high-quality software products. This role requires a strong understanding of software testing principles, automation frameworks, and CI/CD pipelines. You'll be a key influencer in our development process and a strong advocate for quality.

## Responsibilities

- Lead the QA team and provide technical guidance.
- Define testing strategies and methodologies.
- Implement and maintain automation frameworks.
- Integrate testing into the CI/CD pipeline.
- Collaborate with developers and product managers.

**Tech Stack:** Selenium, Cucumber, JUnit, Jenkins, Git, Jira

**Benefits:**
- Generous salary and benefits package.
- Opportunity to shape the future of QA.
- Professional development and training opportunities.
- Collaborative and supportive work environment.
- Flexible work arrangements.

title: Junior Security Analyst
description:
CyberGuard Technologies is seeking a Junior Security Analyst to protect our systems and data from cyber threats. This isn't just a monitoring role; you'll be actively involved in threat hunting, incident response, and vulnerability management. Expect to be challenged.

## Responsibilities

- Monitor security systems and logs for suspicious activity.
- Investigate security incidents and breaches.
- Perform vulnerability assessments and penetration testing.
- Develop and implement security policies and procedures.
- Stay up-to-date on the latest security threats and trends.
- Contribute to security awareness training.
- Automate security tasks using scripting languages.
- Lead incident response efforts and manage security projects.

We require a candidate with 5+ years of experience in cybersecurity, including expertise in threat analysis, incident response, and vulnerability management. Certifications such as CISSP or CEH are highly desirable. A deep understanding of networking protocols and security tools is essential. Experience leading security teams and managing security projects is a must. You will be responsible for making critical security decisions under pressure.

**Benefits:** Competitive salary, comprehensive benefits package, professional development opportunities, cutting-edge technology, opportunity to make a real impact.

title: Junior Python Developer - Machine Learning

- Monitor model performance and identify areas for improvement.
- Write unit tests and integration tests.

**Tech Stack:** Python, Scikit-learn, TensorFlow, PyTorch, AWS

**Benefits:** Learning environment, competitive pay, snacks, flexible work hours.

- Verify defect fixes.
- Automate testing using Selenium or other tools.
- Participate in code reviews.

Knowledge of performance testing and security testing is a plus. You will be responsible for ensuring the quality of our flagship product.

**Benefits:** Competitive hourly rate, flexible schedule, opportunity to learn and grow, supportive team environment, free snacks and coffee.

Certifications such as CCNA or CCNP are highly desirable. A strong understanding of network security principles is essential. Experience leading network teams and managing network projects is a must. You will be responsible for ensuring the reliability and security of our global network.

**Benefits:** Competitive salary, comprehensive benefits package, professional development opportunities, opportunity to work with cutting-edge technology, travel opportunities.

title: Junior QA Tester - Ensuring Quality and Reliability
description:
We're seeking a detail-oriented and enthusiastic Junior QA Tester to join our quality assurance team. You'll be responsible for testing our software applications to ensure they meet our high standards of quality and reliability. This role involves creating test plans, executing test cases, and reporting defects. You'll gain experience with both manual and automated testing techniques. A strong understanding of software testing principles and a passion for finding bugs are essential. You'll collaborate with developers and product managers to improve the overall quality of our products.
